canonical:
  title: 瑞祥花
  author: 鄭沆
  language: lzh
  text: 新祥喜見滿枝春果向今朝得好賓花瑞一家賢瑞國誰收花愛揔移人
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 瑞祥花
  author: 鄭沆
  language: lzh
  text: 新祥喜見滿枝春。果向今朝得好賓。花瑞一家賢瑞國。誰收花愛揔移人。
korean:
  title: 서상화
  author: 정항
  language: kor
  text: |-
    새로운 상서 기꺼이 보노니 가지에 가득한 봄이여
    과연 오늘 아침 반가운 손님을 맞았네
    꽃은 한 집의 상서요 어진 이는 나라의 상서니
    누가 꽃 사랑을 거두어 모두 다 사람에게 옮길꼬
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_020_0500&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Auspicious Blossoms
  author: Jeong Hang
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Fresh omens gladly seen—spring overflowing each branch,
    This very morning welcomed a cherished guest indeed.
    The flowers are one household's blessing, the virtuous man his nation's grace—
    Who will gather this love of flowers and bestow it upon all people?
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The poem employs a traditional parallel structure, with 'flowers' (花) representing personal virtue and 'nation' (國) representing the collective good, a common conceit in classical East Asian poetry where natural beauty mirrors moral excellence.
